      "post_id" : 4645155,
      "comment_id" : 6027274,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
      "body" : "Actually, nowadays I really would almost never use anything else than Strings. I used to advocate for these, but with advances of the JVM it&#39;s almost <b>NEVER</b> necessary anymore, fortunately. If you have a look at the bytecode for the above (at least with a JDK &gt; 1.6u22), you will notice that everything is replaced by a StringBuilder. It&#39;s not only single statements anymore, but actually fairly complicated constructs. I just did several test cases on real-life code, and I actually don&#39;t find any situation where it doesn&#39;t use StringBuilders internally. Quite nice."
